%I A391359 #44 Jun 17 2026 17:38:13
%S A391359 1,98,12,56292,361786618
%N A391359 a(n) is the period of the first differences of S_n(k) where the sequence S_n(k) is the trajectory of 1 under repeated application of the map: m -> m + n-th-smallest number that does not divide m, or -1 if no such orbit exists.
%C A391359 If an orbit with periodic first differences for S_n(k) exists:
%C A391359   S_n(k) = S_n(k-1) + S_n(k-a(n)) - S_n(k-a(n)-1), for k > some offset.
%C A391359   S_n(k+a(n)) = a(n) + c_n, for k > some offset. It is known that c_n is a term from A003418.
%C A391359   The first few c_n for n=1..5 are: 2, 420, 60, 360360, 2677114440.
%C A391359 Other start values may reach eventually the same orbit in at least many if not all cases.
%e A391359 a(2) = 98, because A140485(n + 98) = A140485(n) + 420 for n >= 10, and A140485 is the trajectory of 1 under repeated application of the map: n -> n + second-smallest number that does not divide n.
%e A391359 a(3) = 12, because A140490(n + 12) = A140490(n) + 60 for n >= 13, and A140490 is the trajectory of 1 under repeated application of the map: n -> n + third-smallest number that does not divide n.
%Y A391359 Cf. A003418.
%Y A391359 Cf. A140485-A140494.
%K A391359 nonn,more
%O A391359 1,2
%A A391359 _Thomas Scheuerle_, Jun 06 2026
